main_body:
Article 14 (1) (a) of Regulation (EEC) No 1528/78 is hereby replaced by the following:
'(a) any establishment where:
- either fresh fodder is dehydrated by means of a drier which satisfies the following requirements:
(aa) air temperature at the entry point not less than 93 Â°C;
(bb) residence time of the fodder being dehydrated not exceeding three hours;
(cc) in case of drying in layers of fodder, bed depth of each layer no deeper than one metre;
- or sun-dried fodder is milled;
- or protein concentrates obtained from lucerne or grass juice are manufactured;
- or until 30 April 1987 fodder is dried by artificial means other than that referred to in the first indent and the products dried in this way are milled;'.
